-- XL Unit Doubles Funding Through Credit Agreement to $200 Million
-- B y   M a r c i   J a c o b s
-- 2013-09-12T14:18:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-12/xl-unit-doubles-funding-through-credit-agreement-to-200-million.html
XL Group Plc, the insurer led by
Chief Executive Officer Mike McGavick, said its XLIT subsidiary
doubled the amount of funds available through letters of credit
and revolving loans to $200 million by amending an agreement with
Citigroup Inc.  The unit today amended the agreement reached Aug. 6, Dublin-based XL said in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marci Jacobs in  New York  at 
